---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHero from "../../components/page/PageHero.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy | Virtual Ventures"
  description="Plain English privacy notes for Virtual Ventures visitors, readers, pattern users and future subscribers."
  showFooterBreadcrumbs={false}
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Site Notes"
    title="Privacy"
    description="A plain English note about what Virtual Ventures collects, what is not collected, and what will need updating before new tools go live."
  />

  <main class="page-shell">
    <section class="page-intro">
      <p class="eyebrow">Privacy notes</p>
      <h1>A clear little privacy shelf</h1>
      <p>
        This page is written to be understandable, not scary. It explains the
        current website setup and leaves room for future tools such as a contact
        form or blog email subscription.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-left">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Current site snapshot</h2>
        <p>
          Virtual Ventures is currently mainly a public craft website with blog
          posts, gallery items, pages, RSS, shop links and social links.
        </p>
        <p>
          At the moment, the website does not sell directly through the site,
          does not take payment details, does not create customer accounts, does
          not have comments, and does not have a live email newsletter provider
          connected.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-right">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>What may be used right now</h2>
        <p>
          The website may use normal technical information needed to deliver the
          site, including server or Cloudflare security logs, browser requests,
          page addresses visited and basic device/browser information.
        </p>
        <p>
          The gallery currently uses local storage in your browser to remember
          whether you liked a gallery item. This is stored on your own device and
          is not a customer account or public like count.
        </p>
        <p>
          The search page may place your search words in the page address, for
          example as a search query. That can appear in your browser history and
          may appear in hosting or security logs as part of a normal page request.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-left">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Fonts and outside services</h2>
        <p>
          This website currently loads Google Fonts from Google. Your browser may
          contact Google to fetch those font files unless the site later switches
          to self-hosted fonts.
        </p>
        <p>
          The site is served through Cloudflare. Cloudflare may process technical
          information to deliver the site, improve performance and protect the
          site from unwanted traffic. Cloudflare settings can also add features
          outside the codebase, so those settings need checking before publishing
          this page.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-right">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Contact form</h2>
        <p>
          The contact page is not currently a working contact form in the code I
          checked. When a real contact form is added, this section should be
          updated before it goes live.
        </p>
        <p>
          A future contact form may ask for your name, email address and message
          so Virtual Ventures can reply. The form should show a short notice at
          the point where the message is sent, including where the message goes,
          how long it is kept, and who can access it.
        </p>
        <p>
          Please do not send payment details, passwords, medical details or very
          sensitive personal information through the contact form.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-left">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Future blog subscription</h2>
        <p>
          A blog email subscription is planned but is not live yet. When it is
          added, it should clearly say what people are signing up for before they
          enter their email address.
        </p>
        <p>
          Future subscription notices may include free pattern updates, Thursday
          Crochet and Chatter livestream sections, new videos, optional Etsy PDF
          releases, KDP printed collection news and other Virtual Ventures notes.
        </p>
        <p>
          Provider: [email provider]. Unsubscribe link: [unsubscribe link]. Data
          storage location: [data storage location]. Retention period: [retention
          period].
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-right">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>External platforms</h2>
        <p>
          Virtual Ventures may link to Etsy, Amazon or KDP, YouTube, Feedly and
          social platforms. When you click those links, you leave the Virtual
          Ventures website and the other platform controls its own privacy,
          cookies, accounts, payments and settings.
        </p>
        <p>
          Purchases made on Etsy or Amazon/KDP are handled by those platforms,
          not directly through this website.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-left">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Your choices</h2>
        <p>
          You can choose not to use the future contact form or subscription tool.
          You can also use the RSS feed if you prefer a simple feed reader
          instead of email updates.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you contact Virtual Ventures in future, you can ask about the
          personal information connected to your message or subscription. Contact
          details should be added here before any form or email list goes live:
          [contact email].
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-closing-card">
      <p>
        This page should be reviewed whenever a new form, analytics tool, email
        provider, shop feature, video embed or Cloudflare feature is switched on.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
